                            <comment id="13138596" author="olgan" created="Fri, 28 Oct 2011 19:01:04 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Xuting, thanks for the patch. Since you are catching all parser errors in one place I think you need a more generic message with the context of the error that the parser returns.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13139909" author="xutingz" created="Mon, 31 Oct 2011 04:44:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The test-commit unit tests has been run successfully on this change.&lt;br/&gt;
As this patch only adds log information into Pig, there is no additional unit tests designed for this change.&lt;br/&gt;
Relevant unit test TestParamSubPreproc.java has been successfully run on this change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13142560" author="olgan" created="Wed, 2 Nov 2011 21:25:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Xuting,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch looks good. It is more general than what was originally asked but I believe this is the right patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suggestions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(1) When parameter is in the file, we should give the line in the file where the problem occurs since a file can contain many parameters&lt;br/&gt;
(2) It might be useful to include the parser error to assist in fixing error&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
